techmeme.title: Sources: after Google's monopoly ruling, the DOJ considers options including forcing a breakup of the company or requiring it to share more data with rivals (Bloomberg)
NIST publishes its first three post-quantum cryptography standards; IBM's director of research thinks quantum computing will hit an inflection point around 2030 (Frederic Lardinois/TechCrunch)
Deep-Live-Cam, a deepfake software project that lets users impersonate others on a webcam livestream, goes viral and was briefly the top trending GitHub repo (Benj Edwards/Ars Technica)
Encord, which offers a data labeling tools for AI, raised a $30M Series B led by Next47 and expects to grow its headcount from 70 to 100 by the end of the year (Kyle Wiggers/TechCrunch)
The US Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit ruled that geofence warrants are "prohibited by the Fourth Amendment", at odds with a recent Fourth Circuit ruling (Zack Whittaker/TechCrunch)
